## Common Patterns

```bash
# List with table view
{{structure.name}} <group> <command> --format table

# POST / PUT / PATCH with inline JSON body
{{structure.name}} <group> <command> --data '{"field": "value"}'

# POST / PUT / PATCH with body from file
{{structure.name}} <group> <command> --data @payload.json

# Filter response with jq
{{structure.name}} <group> <command> | jq '.[] | select(.status == "active")'

# Override endpoint (e.g. staging)
{{structure.name}} <group> <command> --endpoint https://staging.example.com

# Verbose: log request method + URL
{{structure.name}} <group> <command> --verbose
```

## Agent Workflow (openapi2cli run --machine)

When using `openapi2cli` as an AI agent tool, use the proxy mode with `--machine`
for structured JSON output at every step:

### Step 1: Discover available operations

```bash
openapi2cli run --oas <spec> --machine
```

Returns a JSON envelope with all operations, groups, and metadata.

### Step 2: Inspect a specific operation

```bash
openapi2cli run --oas <spec> --machine describe <group> <operation>
```

Returns full parameter details, request body schema, response schema,
authentication requirements, and an example command.

### Step 3: Preview the request (dry-run)

```bash
openapi2cli run --oas <spec> --dry-run <group> <operation> --param value
```

Returns the planned HTTP request (method, URL, headers, body) without executing it.

### Step 4: Execute the operation

```bash
openapi2cli run --oas <spec> --machine <group> <operation> --param value
```

Returns the API response wrapped in a structured envelope with timing metadata.

### JSON Envelope Format

Every `--machine` response follows this structure:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": { ... },
  "meta": {
    "operation": "get-item",
    "method": "GET",
    "path": "/items/{id}",
    "baseUrl": "{{structure.baseUrl}}",
    "durationMs": 42
  }
}
```

Error responses:

```json
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "type": "HttpClientError",
    "message": "[HTTP 404 Not Found] ...",
    "statusCode": 404,
    "hint": "Endpoint not found — verify the operation name and path params"
  }
}
```
